<Author>jsmerkle
<Content>Casa Vieja - much more authentic than business hotels I am a single woman and travel to Mexico City for work a few times a year and always stay at the Casa Vieja. My colleagues stay at the business class hotels just a few blocks away, but the Marriott, Hyatt, Nikko, etc. always feel the same no matter where you are. Maybe that's important to some people, but when I'm in Mexico I want to feel like I'm in Mexico! The rooms are extremely spacious, beautifully decorated as others have described. The shower isn't ideal - not sure if it's the water pressure or the hand-held shower head itself, but it's not the best shower I've ever had. But everything else, including the amazing rooftop terrace, feels like you're staying at a 5-star Mexican hacienda.The neighborhood (Polanco) is very upscale and quite safe for strolling around. There is also a Metro station (called Polanco) a few blocks away which will allow you to zip around Mexico City and see all the sights for much less than you'd have to pay a driver. It's very efficient, safe, and the stations have some amazing murals.There are some terrific restaurants in the Polanco area as well - one of which is called Izote, owned by Patricia Quintana. A very gourmet take on traditional Mexican flavors. It's a must-do. The restaurant at Casa Vieja is just so-so, so make sure to get out since Mexico City has some very sophisticated restaurants.My recommendation is to get out of the business class bubble, leave your hotel, and enjoy Mexico! 
