<Content>Intimate and characterful We stayed for 4 nights in April 2007 and loved this boutique hotel. Each bedroom is colourfully decorated and features Mexican fabrics, art and artefacts. The rooms also have kitchens with complimentary coffee. There is a beautiful roof terrace where delicious breakfast and dinner are served. The hotel is located in the very safe Polanco district - we felt perfectly happy wandering about at night, and there were some excellent bars and restaurants within easy walking distance.The hotel staff were very helpful, and arranged an English speaking driver for us for a day. Please note that the previous review appears to refer to a hostel of the same name rather than this hotel. This hotel is definitely upmarket and fairly pricey. 
