<Content>Best hotel I have ever stayed in.... Anyone who loves ambience, wonderful service and location should visit this boutique hotel in Polanco, one of the loveliest spots in Mexico City. Safe, close to all the shops but more importantly, not just another hotel room with a bed and mini bar. The small hotel, only 10 guest suites all feature a kitchen, wonderful continental breakfast served in your kitchen, down duvets and pillows, wonderful little touches like magazines, books about the history of Mexico, live plants and decorated with accessories from all over Mexico. The combination of old world and modern conveniences blend nicely with the incredible service. I ordered a cup of tea one night after shopping and it was at my door before I hung up the phone and crossed the room. If you want something out of the ordinary, this is the place. Antique furniture, hand painted walls, beautiful old tile floors, and the most helpful staff I have ever encountered. 
