<Content>Mexico City- Best Hacienda with 1st Class service, charm, and attention This amazing historic hacienda is the best place I have ever stayed in Mexico. Some of the previous reviews scared me, but they were old reviews. The owner and management of this quaint hotel in the megatropolis of busy Mexico City was so peaceful, romantic, and so much attention is paid to detail, comfort and Mexican History. You feel like you own this historic castle. Located in Polanco (the most expensive and upscale district of Mexico City), you feel so comfortable strolling the street, walking to the park, and taking the metro. I was amazed how safe Mexico City is. Please do not beleive all the poor American Touristy book reviews. I would definitely not go back to Americanized Yucatan Peninsula (Cancun, Cozumel, Riveiera Maya, etc.) Mexico City and the surrounding towns reveal Real Mexico. My private Casa Diego Rivera Suite was beyond my expectations. I traveled solo and I am young. Great for all ages for a spluge. 
