<Content>This hotel is a disaster I visited Mexico City in late November, 2002 and am still trying to get satisfaction from the manager of the Casa Vieja Hotel. I booked and prepaid my room nearly two months in advance, but the day I was to arrive I called to confirm my reservation before leaving my home and was told they had no record of me. After arguing with them for 20 minutes the manager told me not to worry because although they were completely booked he would find a room for me. When I arrived, I indeed had a room and saw only one other guest while I was there. However, in the morning as I left, there was no one at the desk to check me out so I left a note reminding them I had prepaid and that I owed nothing. However, when I received my credit card bill for the card I had offered for incidentals, they had charged me for the stay. I immediately called the manager of the hotel who told me he would take care of it right away. I waited in vain. Many calls and emails later, I still have no satisfaction. They have effectively stolen $360 from me. 
